The paper discusses a technique for generating initial contexts for effective deadlock detection in distributed systems. This involves analyzing possible conflicting task interactions identified by static analysis and discarding other distributed contexts that cannot lead to deadlock. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories.
